WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.770 --> 00:00:05.000
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, DC.

00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:15.930
&gt;&gt; Lee Ann Potter: Good morning!

00:00:15.930 --> 00:00:17.230
&gt;&gt; [Group] Good morning!

00:00:17.230 --> 00:00:19.690
&gt;&gt; Lee Ann Potter:
I'm Lee Ann Potter.

00:00:19.690 --> 00:00:22.880
I direct educational outreach
here at the Library of Congress

00:00:22.880 --> 00:00:25.880
and I am so happy that
all of you are here

00:00:25.880 --> 00:00:27.870
for this really terrific event.

00:00:27.870 --> 00:00:32.350
How many of you -- and I'm going
to ask you guys to turn that --

00:00:32.350 --> 00:00:35.930
dim that light for just a second
so I can see a raise of hands --

00:00:35.930 --> 00:00:39.130
how many of you have
ever tried something new?

00:00:39.130 --> 00:00:43.060
Yeah, I kind of thought so.

00:00:43.060 --> 00:00:45.990
So, you know how when
you try something new,

00:00:45.990 --> 00:00:47.490
you're really excited about it

00:00:47.490 --> 00:00:49.970
and then sometimes you get a
little bit scared about it?

00:00:49.970 --> 00:00:52.090
You know how that is?

00:00:52.090 --> 00:00:57.300
Yeah, well that happens to
all of us and here at --

00:00:57.300 --> 00:00:59.770
well, let me put it this way.

00:00:59.770 --> 00:01:02.630
When you're excited and
even when you're scared,

00:01:02.630 --> 00:01:06.270
it always helps to have
somebody who is encouraging you

00:01:06.270 --> 00:01:09.360
and somebody who is as
enthusiastic and as excited

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:12.570
as you are about whatever
that new thing is, you know?

00:01:12.570 --> 00:01:14.350
And here at the library,

00:01:14.350 --> 00:01:17.430
we've been trying a lot
of new things lately.

00:01:17.430 --> 00:01:21.190
We want to make sure
that everybody knows

00:01:21.190 --> 00:01:25.080
about this amazing library
and its incredible collections

00:01:25.080 --> 00:01:28.310
and how much we can learn
here at the library.

00:01:28.310 --> 00:01:31.810
And when I say we're trying
a whole bunch of new things,

00:01:31.810 --> 00:01:34.020
you know, new things
like maybe, you know,

00:01:34.020 --> 00:01:36.310
inviting a superstar
wrestler/actor

00:01:36.310 --> 00:01:38.750
to come and read a book.

00:01:38.750 --> 00:01:43.850
And fortunately for us, we
have a Librarian of Congress

00:01:43.850 --> 00:01:49.920
who shares our excitement
and encourages and leads us

00:01:49.920 --> 00:01:54.240
with her energy and
her enthusiasm.

00:01:54.240 --> 00:01:57.170
So I am really honored this
morning to be the one who gets

00:01:57.170 --> 00:02:00.560
to introduce you to
Dr. Carla Hayden,

00:02:00.560 --> 00:02:02.690
the 14th Librarian of Congress.

00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:06.560
She earned her PhD at the
University of Chicago.

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:09.990
She began her career as
a children's librarian.

00:02:09.990 --> 00:02:12.530
She led the Pratt
Library in Baltimore.

00:02:12.530 --> 00:02:15.970
She was the president of the
American Library Association.

00:02:15.970 --> 00:02:21.690
And she is absolutely aware
of the power of reading

00:02:21.690 --> 00:02:25.510
and the magic of a good
story -- Dr. Hayden.

00:02:25.510 --> 00:02:30.080
[ Applause ]

00:02:30.080 --> 00:02:32.180
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden: So
what an exciting day.

00:02:32.180 --> 00:02:34.670
You didn't know all that other
stuff that she was saying

00:02:34.670 --> 00:02:37.530
when I was here seeing
how you all are.

00:02:37.530 --> 00:02:42.270
I am so excited because this
is such a special program.

00:02:42.270 --> 00:02:47.890
So I'd like you -- and I got
a chance to meet a lot of you

00:02:47.890 --> 00:02:51.540
and I'm supposed to say here, it
says "Please hold your applause

00:02:51.540 --> 00:02:53.800
until I introduce
all of the schools."

00:02:53.800 --> 00:02:57.830
But let's see how that works.

00:02:57.830 --> 00:03:03.170
I do have to ask you, we have
young people that are not here

00:03:03.170 --> 00:03:04.940
with us in Washington, DC.

00:03:04.940 --> 00:03:08.780
So when we get to them, could
you give them a big hand?

00:03:08.780 --> 00:03:11.170
Because from Washington, DC,

00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:15.460
right here in the Coolidge
Auditorium, we have students

00:03:15.460 --> 00:03:18.510
from Capitol Hill
Montessori School.

00:03:18.510 --> 00:03:23.760
[ Applause ]

00:03:23.760 --> 00:03:27.510
Bishop John T. Walker
School for Boys.

00:03:27.510 --> 00:03:30.400
[ Applause ]

00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:31.700
Plummer Elementary
School [applause].

00:03:31.700 --> 00:03:36.970
Uh-oh, the excitement is rising.

00:03:36.970 --> 00:03:38.420
Kimball Elementary
School [applause].

00:03:38.420 --> 00:03:46.960
Langdon Elementary
School [applause].

00:03:46.960 --> 00:03:50.320
Murray Elementary
